Employers’ Consultative Association (NECA), the voice of business in Nigeria felicitates with an Icon, trail-blazer and doyen of the Accounting profession in Africa, Chief Akintola Williams OFR for reaching another milestone, 100 fruitful and selfless years of service to mankind. Speaking in Lagos, the Director-General of NECA, Mr. Timothy Olawale stated that “Chief Akintola is a model and an embodiment of selfless service both to the nation and to humanity in general. The business community cannot but celebrate this elder statesman and doyen of the accounting profession. A man of many parts with footprints visible for all to see in Nigeria, Chief Akintola is, indeed, worth celebrating.” Powered by RubiQube Ad Network While expressing NECA’s goodwill to the doyen, Mr. Olawale stated that “the Nigeria Employers’ Consultative Association (NECA), felicitates with Chief Akintola on this milestone. We are proud to be associated with him and his organization that has been a member-company of NECA for many years. We wish him good health, sound mind and God’s blessings in the years ahead.”